## Enter Nino Page
enter-nino.title = What is your National Insurance number?
enter-nino.heading = What is {0}’s National Insurance number?
enter-nino.line_1 = It’s on the National Insurance card, benefit letter, payslip or P60. For example, ‘QQ 12 34 56 C’.
enter-nino.line_2 = {0} does not have a National Insurance number
enter-nino.invalid.format.error = Enter a National Insurance number in the correct format


## SA-UTR Page
sa-utr.title = What is {0}’s Unique Taxpayer Reference?
sa-utr.line_1 = This is 10 numbers, for example 1234567890. It will be on tax returns and other letters about Self Assessment. It may be called ‘reference’, ‘UTR’ or ‘official use’.
sa-utr.line_2 = {0} does not have a Unique Taxpayer Reference
sa-utr.details.line_1 = Your UTR helps us identify your business
sa-utr.details.line_2 = I cannot find the UTR
sa-utr.details.line_3 = The business does not have a UTR
sa-utr.error = Enter a Unique Taxpayer Reference in the correct format

